---
permalink: "/{{ page.date | date: '%Y/%m/%d' }}/{{ title | slug }}/index.html"
layout: main-wrapper
# date: this is first publication date of the post
# updates
# - a list of dates that this has been updated on
# comments:
#  tweet:
#    id: ""
#    text: ""
#    dateText: ""
---

<header role="banner" style="{% headerBGStyle cover %} eternal-draft">
  <h1><small>This could one day be a fully completed post on </small> <strong>blog.dermah.com</strong></h1>
</header>
<nav role="navigation">
  <a href="/" >< Back To The Index</a>
</nav>

<main role="main">
  <article>
    <h2><span>{{title}}</span></h2>

    <dl>
      {% if talk %}
      <dt>Presented</dt>
      <dd><time datetime="{{talk.date | date: '%Y-%m-%d'}}">{{talk.date | date: '%e %B %Y'}}</time></dd>
      <br />
      {% endif %}

      <dt>First started</dt>
      <dd><time datetime="{{page.date | date: '%Y-%m-%d'}}">{{page.date | date: '%e %B %Y'}}</time></dd>

      {% if updates %}
      <br />
      <dt>Total updates</dt>
      <dd>{{updates.length}}</dd>

      <br />
      <dt>Last updated</dt>
      <dd><time datetime="{{updates | last | date: '%Y-%m-%d'}}">{{updates | last | date: '%e %B %Y'}}</time></dd>
      {% endif %}
    </dl>
    {{content}}

  <hr />
  <section class="comments">
    <h2><span>Comments</span></h2>

    <p><small>Instead of building a comments section, I've offloaded that job to twitter. You can {% if comments.tweet.id %}reply to this tweet about the post, or{% endif %} just tweet <a href="https://twitter.com/Dermah">@Dermah</a>.</small></p>

    {%- if comments.tweet %}
    <blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-dnt="true" data-theme="light" data-related="Dermah">
      <p lang="en" dir="ltr">
        {{ comments.tweet.text }}
      </p>&mdash; Sputnik (@Dermah) <a href="https://twitter.com/Dermah/status/{{ comments.tweet.id }}?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">{{ comments.tweet.dateString }}</a>
    </blockquote>
    <script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script>
    {%- endif %}

  </section>

  </article>

</main>